I also use proper conventions. So I hope it don't look messy :P. Also I just made some stupid random codes, I just made this for the brackets and [b]NOT[/b] for the codes.

Alright, lets start with the basic. 

A bracket is: { and }

The { opens a code and } closes it.

So lets take a simple code:
[code][size=6pt]
public void example()
{
  if (examplelala == 1)
  {
    lalala = 1;
  }
}
[/size][/code]

You see it open 2 times { and close 2 times }.

So for another example I make this wrong code:

[code][size=6pt]
if(command.equalsIgnoreCase("master")) 
{
  for(int i = 0; i < 21; i++) 
  {
    addSkillXP(14000000, i);
  }
[/size][/code]

Now you see there are 2 open { and only 1 close }. 
[u]This will give 100 errors when you are compiling.[/u]

So under the last bracket of you the you shoud add {. So then it open 2 times and close 2 times.

Now a larze code, it all the time works exact the same.

