You see the int opens. And end on the end. I set a 1 on the begin bracket and a 1 on the end. The others are just opening and closing. You can see this verry easy because I used conversations(also I added figures after evrey bracket so it might be a bit easyer to read, DO NEVER DO THIS IN YOUR REAL CODES LOL :P just do it in your head there). Two styles of conversations: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,281929.0.html I am using the first one because its easyer to read in my opinion.

If you use the way I did it you can never get "100 errors". Also when you are compiling and you got 100 errors it will say in the first error which file the error is in and also the line:

[code]client.java:144: illegal start of expression
        public int maxedStats = 0;
        ^[/code]

Then go in your client.java and hit Ctrl + G, it open a window where you can type the line, so type it there and hit "ok". Most of the time it will go to the end of the code where a bracket is missing or wrong. 

